msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger-west/1945_04_ruhr_pocket/date"
msgid "April 17th, 1945 · Attern, Ruhr, Germany"
msgstr "17 de abril, 1945 - Attern, Ruhr, Alemania"

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger-west/1945_04_ruhr_pocket/doctrine_allround"
msgid "Doctrine: All-Round"
msgstr "Doctrina: Completa"

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger-west/1945_04_ruhr_pocket/doctrine_defensive"
msgid "Doctrine: Defensive"
msgstr "Doctrina: Defensiva"

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger-west/1945_04_ruhr_pocket/doctrine_irregular"
msgid "Doctrine: Irregular"
msgstr "Doctrina: Irregular"

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger-west/1945_04_ruhr_pocket/doctrine_offensive"
msgid "Doctrine: Offensive"
msgstr "Doctrina: Ofensiva"

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger-west/1945_04_ruhr_pocket/fight"
msgid "Fight to the death"
msgstr "Lucha a muerte"

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger-west/1945_04_ruhr_pocket/mission_option_select1"
msgid "Select your Doctrine for the mission:"
msgstr "Seleccione su Estrategia para la misión:"

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger-west/1945_04_ruhr_pocket/name"
msgid "Last stand at the Ruhr"
msgstr "Última batalla en el Ruhr"

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger-west/1945_04_ruhr_pocket/name_big"
msgid "Last stand at the Ruhr"
msgstr "Última batalla en el Ruhr"

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger-west/1945_04_ruhr_pocket/narrator/01"
msgid ""
"Soldaten! The fate of the Fatherland lies in our hands! Unfortunately, our "
"organisation in this sector is currently rather messy! "
msgstr ""
"¡Soldados! ¡El destino de la Patria está en nuestras manos! "
"¡Desgraciadamente, nuestra organización en este sector deja mucho que "
"desear! "

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger-west/1945_04_ruhr_pocket/narrator/02"
msgid ""
"We have been sent here to make things right. You are all veterans of this "
"war, and we will rely on your experience to command the troops to victory."
msgstr ""
"Hemos sido enviados aquí para hacer las cosas bien. Todos ustedes son "
"veteranos de esta guerra, y confiaremos en su experiencia para comandar las "
"tropas hacia la victoria."

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger-west/1945_04_ruhr_pocket/narrator/021"
msgid ""
"Our primary objective is to defend the town of Attern while the local "
"population is being evacuated, or drafted as part of our local defence "
"forces - the Volkssturm."
msgstr ""
"Nuestro principal objetivo es defender la ciudad de Attern mientras la "
"población local es evacuada, o reclutada como parte de nuestras fuerzas de "
"defensa local - la Volkssturm."

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger-west/1945_04_ruhr_pocket/narrator/03"
msgid ""
"So far, our Volkssturm defense forces have performed poorly, commanded by "
"utterly incompetent Gauleiters. Your first task is to find the volkssturm "
"batallion and recruit as many of them as you can. Teach them some real "
"tactics!"
msgstr ""
"Hasta ahora, nuestras fuerzas de defensa Volkssturm han funcionado "
"penosamente, comandadas por Gauleiters totalmente incompetentes. Tu primera "
"tarea es encontrar el batallón volkssturm y reclutar a tantos como puedas. "
"¡Enséñales tácticas de verdad!"

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger-west/1945_04_ruhr_pocket/narrator/04"
msgid ""
"We also require you to recover any damaged vehicles or abandoned equipment "
"in order to ready them for use against the Americans."
msgstr ""
"También le pedimos que recupere cualquier vehículo dañado o equipo "
"abandonado para prepararlos para su uso contra los americanos."

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger-west/1945_04_ruhr_pocket/narrator/05"
msgid ""
"Members of the Volkssturm! We are what's left of of the 116th Panzer "
"Division. The Americans are closing in! We have learnt how to fight them "
"after the Normandy landings. Join us and you might survive the next enemy "
"onslaught."
msgstr ""
"¡Miembros de la Volkssturm! Somos lo que queda de la 116ª División Panzer. "
"¡Los americanos se acercan! Hemos aprendido a luchar contra ellos tras el "
"desembarco de Normandía. Uníos a nosotros y podréis sobrevivir al próximo "
"ataque enemigo."

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger-west/1945_04_ruhr_pocket/narrator/06"
msgid ""
"Pick 10 Volkssturm soldiers. They will be under your command. I will lead "
"the others."
msgstr ""
"Elige 10 soldados Volkssturm. Estarán bajo su mando. Yo dirigiré a los demás."

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger-west/1945_04_ruhr_pocket/narrator/07"
msgid ""
"Herr Leutnant, the enemy is approaching on the main road. Set up an ambush! "
"Use the high ground and let it rain Panzerfausts. There are extra "
"Panzerfausts in the boxes."
msgstr ""
"Herr Leutnant, el enemigo se acerca por la carretera principal. ¡Preparen "
"una emboscada! Usa el terreno elevado y haz que lluevan los Panzerfausts. "
"Hay Panzerfausts extra en las cajas."

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger-west/1945_04_ruhr_pocket/narrator/08"
msgid ""
"The Americans are losing troops and realise that this sector is still "
"hostile. They brought in heavy artillery to obliterate the town. We cannot "
"let them do this! But since they don't know that you have dealt with their "
"column, you can use the element of surprise against them!"
msgstr ""
"Los americanos están perdiendo tropas y se han dado cuenta de que este "
"sector sigue siendo hostil. Trajeron artillería pesada para arrasar la "
"ciudad. ¡No podemos dejar que lo hagan! Pero como no saben que te has "
"ocupado de su columna, ¡puedes usar el factor sorpresa contra ellos!"

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger-west/1945_04_ruhr_pocket/narrator/09"
msgid ""
"Good job! Now fall back to our main defensive line. Morale isn't great. Go "
"to the main square and recruit any troops you see. Prepare to defend Attern."
msgstr ""
"¡Buen trabajo! Ahora volvamos a nuestra línea defensiva principal. La moral "
"no está muy alta. Ve a la plaza principal y recluta las tropas que veas. "
"Prepárate para defender Attern."

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger-west/1945_04_ruhr_pocket/narrator/10"
msgid "They're coming. This is our last chance! Make it count!"
msgstr "Ya vienen. ¡Es nuestra última oportunidad! ¡Haz que valga la pena!"

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger-west/1945_04_ruhr_pocket/narrator/11"
msgid "Excellent job Soldaten. The Americans are backing off."
msgstr "Excelente trabajo Soldaten. Los americanos están retrocediendo."

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger-west/1945_04_ruhr_pocket/narrator/fight1"
msgid ""
"Soldaten! The enemy has offered terms of unconditional surrender but we have "
"chosen to fight! We haven't fought them all the way from Normandy to here, "
"just to bow down to them now!"
msgstr ""
"¡Soldados! ¡El enemigo nos ha ofrecido la rendición incondicional, pero "
"hemos elegido luchar! ¡No llevamos luchado contra ellos desde Normandía para "
"inclinarnos ante ellos ahora!"

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger-west/1945_04_ruhr_pocket/narrator/fight2"
msgid ""
"We will die defending the Fatherland, like our fathers and grandfathers did. "
"Let our actions today be the tales inspiring our grandchildren! For Germany!!"
msgstr ""
"Moriremos defendiendo la Patria, como hicieron nuestros padres y abuelos. "
"¡Que nuestras acciones de hoy sean las historias que inspiren a nuestros "
"nietos! ¡Por Alemania!"

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger-west/1945_04_ruhr_pocket/narrator/fight3"
msgid ""
"Thank you for showing respect to my troops. These men all deserved long and "
"happy lives in peace."
msgstr ""
"Gracias por mostrar respeto a mis tropas. Todos estos hombres merecían una "
"vida larga y feliz en paz."

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger-west/1945_04_ruhr_pocket/narrator/grille"
msgid "What is that thing there? Get that Grille crewed and operational!"
msgstr "¿Qué es eso? ¡Pongan en funcionamiento y monten ese Grille!"

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger-west/1945_04_ruhr_pocket/narrator/offer"
msgid ""
"Herr Leutnant, you and your men have earned the respect of both me and our "
"American adversaries. It is only fair for you to decide the fate of our "
"unit. We will stand by your decision. Make the choice, Herr Leutnant."
msgstr ""
"Herr Leutnant, usted y sus hombres se han ganado el respeto tanto mío como "
"de nuestros adversarios americanos. Es justo que usted decida el destino de "
"nuestra unidad. Respaldaremos su decisión. Tome su decisión, Herr Leutnant."

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger-west/1945_04_ruhr_pocket/narrator/offer1"
msgid "I command this element of the 116th Panzer Division. What do you want?"
msgstr ""
"Estoy al mando de este elemento de la 116ª División Panzer. ¿Qué es lo que "
"quiere?"

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger-west/1945_04_ruhr_pocket/narrator/offer2"
msgid ""
"You want us to surrender, then? Avoiding bloodshed after you obliterated "
"this town?"
msgstr ""
"¿Quieres que nos rindamos, entonces? ¿Evitar el derramamiento de sangre "
"después de haber arrasado esta ciudad?"

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger-west/1945_04_ruhr_pocket/narrator/ostwind"
msgid ""
"An Ostwind has been left abandoned in these high grounds. We should "
"definitely repair and re-service it."
msgstr ""
"Un Ostwind ha sido abandonado en estas alturas. Deberíamos repararlo y "
"volver a darle servicio."

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger-west/1945_04_ruhr_pocket/narrator/pak40"
msgid "Look! An abandoned PaK-40. I think we could make good use of that."
msgstr "¡Mirad! Un PaK-40 abandonado. Creo que podríamos darle un buen uso."

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger-west/1945_04_ruhr_pocket/narrator/pak9738"
msgid ""
"A well positioned pak gun in the hill! Yes, very good. We should use it."
msgstr ""
"¡Un cañón PaK bien posicionado en la colina! Sí, muy bien. Deberíamos usarlo."

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger-west/1945_04_ruhr_pocket/narrator/pershing"
msgid ""
"What the hell is that tank coming down the road? It doesn't look like a "
"Sherman. Have the Americans learnt how to build proper tanks?"
msgstr ""
"¿Qué demonios es ese tanque que viene por la carretera? No parece un "
"Sherman. ¿Han aprendido los americanos a construir tanques de verdad?"

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger-west/1945_04_ruhr_pocket/narrator/surrender1"
msgid "Soldaten! You have fought bravely and proudly for your country!"
msgstr "¡Soldados! ¡Habéis luchado valiente y orgullosamente por vuestro país!"

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger-west/1945_04_ruhr_pocket/narrator/surrender2"
msgid ""
"In spite of our best efforts, this war is now over for us. Do not feel "
"ashamed, do not feel dishonoured."
msgstr ""
"A pesar de nuestros esfuerzos, esta guerra ha terminado para nosotros. No os "
"avergoncéis, no os sintáis deshonrados."

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger-west/1945_04_ruhr_pocket/narrator/surrender3"
msgid ""
"Your enemies have feared you. Your enemies have respected you. We have waged "
"our war honorably and gallantly."
msgstr ""
"Tus enemigos han sentido temor. Os han mostrado respeto. Hemos librado "
"nuestra guerra con honor y gallardía."

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger-west/1945_04_ruhr_pocket/narrator/surrender4"
msgid ""
"You've seen death and you suffered together. But now, you should all return "
"to your families and live the rest of your life in peace."
msgstr ""
"Habéis visto la muerte y la habéis sufrido juntos. Pero ahora, todos debéis "
"volver con vuestras familias y vivir el resto de vuestra vida en paz."

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger-west/1945_04_ruhr_pocket/narrator/surrender5"
msgid ""
"But do so looking up at the clear skies, and not down at your feet! Germany "
"will recover for sure."
msgstr ""
"Pero hazlo mirando al cielo despejado, ¡y no a tus pies! Alemania se "
"recuperará seguro."

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger-west/1945_04_ruhr_pocket/narrator/surrender6"
msgid ""
"I'm proud to have served with each and every one of you. From the shores of "
"Normandy to the heart of our country, We've defended Fortress Europe "
"together; you made your country proud."
msgstr ""
"Estoy orgulloso de haber servido con todos y cada uno de vosotros. Desde las "
"costas de Normandía hasta el corazón de nuestro país, hemos defendido juntos "
"la Fortaleza Europa; habéis hecho que vuestro país se sienta orgulloso."

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger-west/1945_04_ruhr_pocket/narrator/surrender7"
msgid ""
"We hereby surrender to the US Armed Forces. There is no other way to survive "
"this bloodshed, this hell!"
msgstr ""
"Por la presente nos rendimos a las Fuerzas Armadas de los EE.UU. ¡No hay "
"otra forma de sobrevivir a este derramamiento de sangre, a este infierno!"

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger-west/1945_04_ruhr_pocket/narrator_usa/fight1"
msgid ""
"Well, Sir, that's the best we could do. Your men deserved a proper burial "
"after the fight they put up. "
msgstr ""
"Bueno, señor, es lo mejor que pudimos hacer. Sus hombres merecían un "
"entierro apropiado después de la pelea que dieron. "

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger-west/1945_04_ruhr_pocket/narrator_usa/fight2"
msgid ""
"Unfortunately, you do need to come with us now... Soldiers, please escort "
"the german commander back to HQ."
msgstr ""
"Desafortunadamente, tiene que venir con nosotros ahora... Soldados, por "
"favor escolten al comandante alemán de vuelta al cuartel general."

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger-west/1945_04_ruhr_pocket/narrator_usa/offer1"
msgid ""
"German Soldiers! We are company commanders from the 7th Armored and 99th "
"Infantry. You have fought hard today. With whom do we have the pleasure of "
"speaking?"
msgstr ""
"¡Soldados alemanes! Somos comandantes de compañía del 7º Blindado y del 99º "
"de Infantería. Han luchado bien hoy. ¿Con quién tenemos el placer de hablar?"

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger-west/1945_04_ruhr_pocket/narrator_usa/offer2"
msgid ""
"We have come with an offer which could be of great interest for us all! Your "
"war is lost. There is no need for more bloodshed. "
msgstr ""
"¡Hemos venido con una oferta que podría ser de gran interés para todos "
"nosotros! Vuestra guerra está perdida. No hay necesidad de más derramamiento "
"de sangre. "

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger-west/1945_04_ruhr_pocket/narrator_usa/offer3"
msgid ""
"You are surrounded and severely outnumbered. Lay down your arms, and we will "
"take good care of your men. We will give you food and medical attention, and "
"help you bury your dead."
msgstr ""
"Están rodeados y severamente superados en número. Depongan las armas y "
"cuidaremos bien de sus hombres. Les daremos comida y atención médica, y les "
"ayudaremos a enterrar a sus muertos."

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger-west/1945_04_ruhr_pocket/narratorhint/01"
msgid ""
"In order to recruit soldiers, move your units close and hover over the "
"soldier you want to recruit. A grabbing icon will appear. Inspect the troops "
"and click to recruit 10 soldiers of your choice."
msgstr ""
"Para reclutar soldados, acerca tus unidades y pasa el ratón por encima del "
"soldado que quieras reclutar. Aparecerá un icono de selección. Inspecciona "
"las tropas y haz clic para reclutar a 10 soldados de tu elección."

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger-west/1945_04_ruhr_pocket/outro_completed"
msgid ""
"This is the end. Regardless of the choice you just made, there will be no "
"medals, just a lot of graves. You will need to roll up your sleeves and "
"start building back your country and make sure that a senseless war like "
"this will not repeat itself. Well done!"
msgstr ""
"Este es el final. Independientemente de la elección que acabas de hacer, no "
"habrá medallas, sólo un montón de tumbas. Tendréis que arremangaros, empezar "
"a reconstruir vuestro país y aseguraros de que una guerra sin sentido como "
"esta no se repita. ¡Bien hecho!"

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger-west/1945_04_ruhr_pocket/outro_failed"
msgid ""
"This failure will have consequences. For one, we cannot prevent being "
"surrounded anymore; furthermore, the road to Berlin is now open to the "
"Americans. Who will tell General von Waldenburg the bad news?"
msgstr ""
"Este fracaso tendrá consecuencias. Por un lado, ya no podemos evitar que nos "
"rodeen; además, el camino a Berlín está ahora abierto para los americanos. "
"¿Quién le dará las malas noticias al general von Waldenburg?"

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger-west/1945_04_ruhr_pocket/place"
msgid "116th Panzer Division"
msgstr "116ª División Panzer"

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger-west/1945_04_ruhr_pocket/skip"
msgid "Skip preparation phase"
msgstr "Saltar la fase de preparación"

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger-west/1945_04_ruhr_pocket/story"
msgid " It is now April 1945. A few weeks ago, the Ludendorff bridge at Remagen was captured intact. The Allies also crossed the Rhine at Wesel and Nierstein. As a result, army group B has become encircled completely; the stage for the battle of the Ruhr pocket has been set.\n\n You and the 116th Panzer division have been directed to the area south of Iserlohn. Your first problem is the wide area over which your troops have been dispersed in the past few days; they’re literally everywhere, which makes it impossible for them to act as a unit.\n\n You should group all available troops and see whether you can find any supplies and equipment that was abandoned during yesterday’s fighting, before you can even think about any coordinated actions. Use your experience to make the most of this difficult situation. Do not despair, wonder weapons will soon tip the balance of the war in our favor.\n\nGood luck!"
msgstr ""
"Estamos en abril de 1945.\n"
"\n"
"Hace unas semanas, el puente Ludendorff en Remagen\n"
"\n"
"fue capturado intacto.\n"
"\n"
"Los aliados también cruzaron el Rin en Wesel y Nierstein.\n"
"\n"
"Como resultado, el grupo de ejército B ha quedado completamente cercado;\n"
"\n"
"el escenario para la batalla del cerco del Ruhr ha sido establecido.\n"
"\n"
"\n"
"\n"
"Usted y la 116 ª División Panzer se han dirigido a\n"
"\n"
"el área al sur de Iserlohn.\n"
"\n"
"Su primer problema es la amplia zona en la que sus\n"
"\n"
"tropas se han dispersado en los últimos días;\n"
"\n"
"están literalmente en todas partes, lo que hace imposible\n"
"\n"
"para ellos actuar como una unidad.\n"
"\n"
"\n"
"\n"
"Debe agrupar todas las tropas disponibles y ver si\n"
"\n"
"puede encontrar los suministros y equipos que fueron abandonados\n"
"\n"
"durante los combates de ayer, antes de que puedas siquiera pensar\n"
"\n"
"en cualquier acción coordinada.\n"
"\n"
"Utilice su experiencia para sacar el máximo provecho de esta difícil\n"
"\n"
"situación. No desesperes, las maravillosas armas pronto inclinarán\n"
"\n"
"la balanza de la guerra a nuestro favor.\n"
"\n"
"\n"
"\n"
"¡Buena suerte!"

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger-west/1945_04_ruhr_pocket/surrender"
msgid "Surrender"
msgstr "Rendición"

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger-west/1945_04_ruhr_pocket/task1"
msgid "Go to the local Volkssturm forces and recruit 10 soldiers."
msgstr "Ve a las fuerzas locales del Volkssturm y recluta a 10 soldados."

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger-west/1945_04_ruhr_pocket/task2"
msgid "Recover at least 2 AT guns."
msgstr "Recupera al menos 2 armas AT."

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger-west/1945_04_ruhr_pocket/task3"
msgid "Recover and repair at least 2 tanks."
msgstr "Recuperar y reparar al menos 2 tanques."

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger-west/1945_04_ruhr_pocket/task4"
msgid "Ambush the American column."
msgstr "Emboscar a la columna americana."

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger-west/1945_04_ruhr_pocket/task5"
msgid "Take out the heavy artillery."
msgstr "Eliminar la artillería pesada."

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger-west/1945_04_ruhr_pocket/task6"
msgid "Regroup at the town of Attern and defend it!"
msgstr "¡Reagrúpate en la ciudad de Attern y defiéndela!"

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger-west/1945_04_ruhr_pocket/task7"
msgid "Choose: Surrender or fight to the last man"
msgstr "Elige: Rendirse o luchar hasta el último hombre"

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger-west/1945_04_ruhr_pocket/timer"
msgid "US column will arrive in:"
msgstr "La columna estadounidense llegará en:"

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger-west/1945_04_ruhr_pocket/timer2"
msgid "US attack will commence in:"
msgstr "El ataque de EE.UU. comenzará en:"

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger-west/1945_04_ruhr_pocket/timer3"
msgid "Defend Attern!"
msgstr "¡Defiende Attern!"

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger-west/1945_04_ruhr_pocket/timer4"
msgid "Choose the fate of your troops:"
msgstr "Elige el destino de tus tropas:"

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger-west/1945_04_ruhr_pocket/win"
msgid ""
"You chose to fight, your soldiers did the ultimate sacrifice for the "
"Fatherland, and the enemy has buried your troops with honours out of "
"admiration for your fighting spirit."
msgstr ""
"Eligieron luchar, sus soldados hicieron el último sacrificio por la Patria, "
"y el enemigo ha enterrado a sus tropas con honores por admiración a su "
"espíritu de lucha."

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger-west/1945_04_ruhr_pocket/win2"
msgid ""
"You chose to surrender to the US forces, and spare the lives of your men in "
"a desperate situation against overwhelming odds. The enemy will take good "
"care of your troops out of respect for the tenacious fighting spirit. Soon, "
"Germany will capitulate and the troops will be able to go back to their "
"families."
msgstr ""
"Has optado por rendirte a las fuerzas estadounidenses y perdonar la vida a "
"tus hombres en una situación desesperada contra unas probabilidades "
"abrumadoras. El enemigo cuidará bien de tus tropas por respeto a su tenaz "
"espíritu de lucha. Pronto, Alemania capitulará y las tropas podrán volver "
"con sus familias."
